	<dita:topic xmlns="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="publication">
    <title>publication <lnpid>id-CA14-35631</lnpid></title>

    <body>
        <section>
            <p><sourcexml>publication</sourcexml> becomes
                    <targetxml>doc:metadata/pubinfo:pubinfo/pubinfo:publicationname</targetxml>.</p></section>
        <section><p><b>Trademarks and related marks:</b> When (TM) or (R) occur in
                    <sourcexml>publication</sourcexml>, convert to unicode code point as
                follows:</p>
            <p><b>(TM)</b> becomes &amp;#8482;
                <b>(R)</b> becomes &amp;#174;</p>
        </section>

        <!-- removed mapping for (MC) because entity not supported as of Sep 4 2015.  JMcNally -->
        <!--<b>(MC)</b> becomes <![CDATA[&#127338;]]>-->

        <example>
            <title>Example 1</title>
            <codeblock>
&lt;dig:info&gt;
    &lt;publication&gt;Carlson Personal Injury Quantum of Damages NetLetter(TM)&lt;/publication&gt;
&lt;/dig:info&gt;
       </codeblock>
            <b>becomes</b>
            <codeblock>
&lt;doc:metadata&gt;
    &lt;pubinfo:pubinfo&gt;
        &lt;pubinfo:publicationname&gt;Carlson Personal Injury Quantum of Damages
            NetLetter&amp;#8482;&lt;/pubinfo:publicationname&gt;
    &lt;/pubinfo:pubinfo&gt;
&lt;/doc:metadata&gt;
       </codeblock>
        </example>
        <note>Conversion should not create consecutive <targetxml>pubinfo:pubinfo</targetxml>
            elements. When 2 or more consecutive sibling source elements map to
                <targetxml>pubinfo:pubinfo</targetxml>, data should be merged to a single
                <targetxml>pubinfo:pubinfo</targetxml> element unless this would hamper content
            ordering.</note>
        <section>
            <title>Changes</title>
            <p>2015-09-06: <ph id="change_20150906_jm">Modified rule for trademarks. No longer
                    converting (MC) to entity, the unicode code point is not currently supported.
                    The pcdata (MC) is retained instead. RFA 145.</ph></p>
            <p>2015-05-05: <ph id="change_20150505_PS">Added note to covert (TM), (R), and (MC) to
                    unicode code points. DB # 45. Applicable to CA14.</ph></p>
            <p>2015-02-20: <ph id="change_20150220_PS">Created.</ph></p>
        </section>
    </body>
